description: {"blocks":[{"key":"27ktn","text":"Phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) is a buffer solution (pH ~7.4) commonly used in biological research. It is a water-based salt solution containing disodium hydrogen phosphate, sodium chloride and optionally, potassium chloride and potassium dihydrogen phosphate. The buffer helps to maintain a constant pH.
